THE Gauteng Department of Education 2019 online registration for grades one and eight went live on Monday morning.Many parents went to social media, to say the process was better this year as compared to the technical glitches they faced last year.The education department says it has improved the system, in light of the problems they faced previously.if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>According to MEC Panyaza Lesufi, those parents who don't know how to use the system can visit any community library for help.In order to make the registration process simple and faster the Department of Home Affairs has also been brought on board.Bringing in the department, will help in the process of applying on-line, the parents have to key-in their South African I.D number and it will automatically fill in the parent's details, taken from the Home Affairs department's database.